    public interface DynamicDevice
extends NameTag, IDynamicSimulation
    A representation of the model object 'Dynamic Device'. Base class for defining dynamic device

    The following features are supported:

    • Scripts
    • Extended Device Id
    See Also:
    DstabDevicePackage.getDynamicDevice()

      • getExtendedDeviceId

        java.lang.String getExtendedDeviceId()
        Returns the value of the 'Extended Device Id' attribute. Currently the device Id (like "1" or "A") is for specifying the same type of devices attached to the same bus. As we have DynamicDeviceList that includes generators and loads, etc, extendedDeviceId is needed to differentiate them and ideally should be unique in the whole system. An example of extendedDeviceId is "Machine_1@Bus1".
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Extended Device Id' attribute.
        See Also:
        setExtendedDeviceId(String), DstabDevicePackage.getDynamicDevice_ExtendedDeviceId()
